# OpenCode Configuration for Alpha Project

## Project Context
Alpha is a business directory platform with React frontend and Bun/Elysia backend.

## Development Workflow
1. Always kill existing processes before starting:
   - `powershell -Command "Get-Process java -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force"`
   - `powershell -Command "Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 5173 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | ForEach-Object { Stop-Process -Id $_.OwningProcess -Force }"`
   - `powershell -Command "Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 3000 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | ForEach-Object { Stop-Process -Id $_.OwningProcess -Force }"`
   - Verify processes are killed: `timeout /t 2 /nobreak >nul && powershell -Command "if (Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 5173 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue) { Write-Host 'WARNING: Port 5173 still in use' -ForegroundColor Yellow }" && powershell -Command "if (Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 3000 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue) { Write-Host 'WARNING: Port 3000 still in use' -ForegroundColor Yellow }" && powershell -Command "if (Get-Process java -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue) { Write-Host 'WARNING: Java processes still running' -ForegroundColor Yellow }"`
2. Backend runs on port 3000: `cd packages/backend-java && ./gradlew bootRun`
3. Frontend runs on port 5173: `cd packages/web && npm run dev`
4. Database runs on port 5433 (PostgreSQL)

## Code Conventions
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Follow existing patterns in codebase
- Fix root causes, not symptoms
- Never use mock data when real API/database is available
- Handle CORS properly (no Vite proxy)

## Testing Requirements
- Run tests after significant changes
- Backend: `cd packages/backend-java && ./gradlew test`
- Frontend: `cd packages/web && npm run test`

## Environment
- Single .env file in root directory
- CORS_ORIGIN includes http://localhost:5173 and http://localhost:5179
- Database connection: postgresql://alpha_user:alpha_password@localhost:5433/alpha

## Common Tasks
- Database migrations: `./gradlew flywayMigrate`
- Build application: `./gradlew build`
- Run application: `./gradlew bootRun`
- Build frontend: `npm run build`